data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. Welcome home! This beautiful four-bedroom, two bathroom house with a three year old roof, is perfect for first time homebuyers, families, and investors alike. Situated on a large lot, this property offers plenty of space for outdoor activities. As you enter, you'll immediately notice the elegant floor plan with arched architectural details and soaring vaulted ceilings. The formal living and dining areas seamlessly flow into the kitchen and family room, creating the ideal environment for entertaining guests or enjoying a cozy night in with the family. The sunlit dining space is perfect for savoring a family meal or hosting a dinner party. The kitchen features bar top seating, stainless steel appliances, pantry storage, and convenient access to the backyard through sliding glass doors. Retreat to the primary bedroom complete with a walk-in closet, tall vaulted ceilings, and an en-suite bath with ample counter space and a glass door shower. Three additional bright and airy guest bedrooms provide plenty of space for family and friends. The guest bath features extra counter space and a tub/shower combo. Step outside to the spacious fenced backyard with a concrete patio, perfect for barbecues or simply enjoying the Florida sunshine. The nearby Wes Crile Park offers basketball courts, a softball field, outdoor fitness equipment, a splash pad, playground, and more. Take advantage of the quick access to I4, shopping, and dining. Spend your weekends exploring Lake Monroe or swimming among the manatees at Blue Springs. Enjoy the slower paced country life while having the modern convenience of everything you need close by. Don't miss out on the opportunity to call this house your home—call today to schedule a showing!  Seller to credit buyer with a $5k credit towards closing costs!   Brand new tile flooring material included with the sale of home!
